often overlooked masterpiece read this to understand sting 's `` tea in the sahara '' reference for the first time , and to your very core . ( we 're all looking for the tallest sand dune -- the place with the optimal vantage point -- and we often lose our way in deserts of our own making . ) what an amazing book . i 'm so glad i believed gore vidal 's cover blurb about bowles ' art far exceeding that of other contemporary american writers . really , vidal says it best : `` bowles has glimpsed what lies back of our sheltering sky ... an endless flux of stars so like those atoms which make us up that we experience not only horror but likeness . '' beg , borrow , or buy at least a cheap paperback version : if you do n't read the sheltering sky , you 're missing out on greatness